Flames shot from Thassalin's jaws as the gigantic Thracian set a particular woodland area ablaze and then circled above it to spot any movements. Strangely, the eerie screeching behind him subsided as he slowed down. Thassalin had forgotten the passengers on his back.
"What's going on, Tenuk, you've already turned into a Thracian once!"
"If I fly myself, it's completely different from suddenly being lifted up by a giant pink dragon!"
"Was was so bad, or, Kayel?"
Kayel clearly wasn't of Nyssis opinion. He looked less black than usual and his claws had dug so deeply into Thassalin's back that the Thracian was bleeding. However, Thassalin seemed not to mind. Nonetheless, he realized he had frightened his new friends and landed on a clearing.
"SORRY, BUT I SMELLED SOMETHING. I HAD TO TAKE CARE OF IT!"
"Did you have to drag us along too?" Tenuk growled as he climbed off Thassalin's back and slid down his tail. "And we left Retvik behind! We abandoned our big, strong warrior! How is he supposed to catch up with us?"
"He will come up with something...," Nyssis growled. "Retvik isn't the fastest, but he's not dumb."
"Sure, but can Retvik drive?"
Nyssis winked and turned back to Tenuk. "Of course he can drive."
"Have you ever seen Retvik drive a vehicle? He doesn't have a truck like yours, and I haven't seen him drive any fancy little car like Kayel's either. Besides, he only started taking the car for work because you always drive us. He only has his bicycle."
Echoes of laughter interrupted them. Thassalin suddenly found something incredibly funny, but no one knew what he was laughing at. It took him a bit too long to calm down.
"SORRY, BUT I HAD TO INTRODUCE YOUR GIANT FRIEND IN ARMOR ON SUCH A TINY BICYCLE FOR TEMTHAN-KIDS. THAT WAS PRICELESS! I WISH I HAD SOME KIND OF TELEPATHY. WHAT A FANTASTIC IDEA! ONE I CAN'T SHARE!"
Kayel chuckled, imagining what was going on in Thassalin's head. "Yes, okay. But what did you smell, and why did you suddenly take off?"
Thassalin grunted, took off, and disappeared. When he returned after a short while, he threw something lifeless in front of Nyssis feet. It was an Orothrack, a very rare, pale gold dragon creature, but it was missing its head. "YET ANOTHER DEAD ONE. I HEAR THEIR SHOUTS. SMELL YOUR BLOOD. SOMETHING PUSHS ME TO PROTECT AND CHASE. AS YISINI COMMANDS. THEY ARE VERY NEAR."
The powerful Thrakian suddenly froze. Nyssi and Kayel also froze and looked attentively at a gap in the clearing. Something large and black stared at them and hissed. Whatever it was, it spread two enormous wings and shot towards Thassalin, ignoring the three smaller creatures in between. Kayel and Tenuk just managed to seek cover, but Nyssis was dragged along and almost thrown onto Thassalin.
Thassalin reacted to this attack by snatching Nyssi and tossing him onto his back with his incredibly long, agile tail before taking off into the air himself. The black, double-winged creature followed them at high speed.
Kayel snapped irritably as he took his rifle off his back and opened a bag that contained a ammunition belt, hung the belt over his chest, but quickly realized that Nyssi, the Thraki, and the monster were out of sight.
"Hey, Tenuk, could you transform into something that can fly?" asked Kayel.
"Do you want to follow them?"
"Yes, of course!"
"But... One of them is a huge monster!"
"Yes and? I'm standing here with a high-caliber rifle in hand and could start shooting right now. But, well, how should I put it – I need to be able to see it to hit it."
Tenuk hesitated, then stepped back to have more space. With a soft, painful grunting sound, Tenuks body stretched, his fur turned into scales, and his arms became wings. He quickly transformed into a normal, light blue Thracian, but his eyes remained red.
"Mount up."
Like a normally appearing Thracian, Tenuk now had a proper scaled shield running along his back. Conveniently, he also had grown a pair of spines on his back where Kayel could grip. It took a bit too long for Tenuk to get airborne, but once in the air, he quickly oriented himself and tried to take up the pursuit.
Tenuk and Kayel soon realized they were not alone. A second dark creature shot upwards beneath them, and Tenuk barely managed to avoid a collision.
"That must be the other terrifying giant monster Lanex was afraid of?" Kayel frowned. He tried to shoot at the second beast, missed, and quickly reloaded.
Tenuk did not answer. He was too focused on preparing for the flight towards Nyssi and Thassalin, even though the other creature was pursuing them. Kayel awkwardly turned around to keep the monster in his sights. The fact that it was chasing them was an advantage for Kayel, as it allowed him to aim and shoot more easily. Two shots went through the upper wings of the creature, which howled in pain and sank back under the trees. Kayel wasn't sure if it was still following them, but it definitely wouldn't be able to keep up with them.
A good distance ahead, Nyssi clung desperately while Thassalin swung around and spat flames at the blackened monster. The creature was clearly injured. It seemed furious but not ready to give up. The fireballs didn't seem to have the desired effect. When Thassalin stretched out, Nyssi took the opportunity to draw her own weapon, an old reliable shotgun. Although it wasn't exactly the first choice, perhaps the shot would deter the black beast.
